{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78414988-7b17-4330-b335-87f48e9dca1b","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote: xUnit embeds the skip reason directly in `[Fact]`/`[Theory]` rather than using a separate attribute. The other three all use a standalone attribute alongside `[TestMethod]` or `[Test]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7a1a80d8-abbe-4bba-a3a8-6a4db1716c20","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":330,"requestId":"5C33:1ECD:ED270:1314A7:69F54ECC"},"id":"593dbcdf-0431-48af-b9ad-82e4484cbbca","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:09:39.531Z","parentId":"2ff1164e-e594-4b95-a297-51b3c7db3f3f"}
